Rating: 4
OH WOW, people! I had first tried this recipe a few years ago, and took advice from 3 reviewers from 9/23-11/01/03, then tweaked myself. Here's my recipe for making 2 loaves (which will NOT last long!): 3/4 c. + 4 T. sour cream with 1 T. baking soda; 2 sticks butter, 1 2/3- 3/4 c. sugar (I like it less, no one misses it), 1 T. vanilla extract, 4 eggs, 2 c. mashed very ripe banana (about 3, even out measure with apple sauce), 4 c. flour (half all- purpose, half whole wheat pastry flour) whisked together with 1 t. baking powder, 2 t. salt, 1 1/2 t. cinnamon, 1/2 t. nutmeg and 1 t. cardamom (amazing!); 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup mini chocolate chips lightly coated with flour. Follow recipe directions, baking for 65-70 minutes as suggested, checking with toothpick for doneness. This makes a super moist and delicious banana bread! (*I once added about 1 1/2 T. ground flaxseed for a healthy kick, but it cuts baking time because the oil in it makes them brown faster). ENJOY!

