This recipe is indeed delicious, but it is also way too sweet and terribly fatty. So I've modified the recipe and found a slightly more healthful version that is very flavorful and moist: - replace sour cream with low-fat vanilla yoghurt - recommended baking soda - reduce butter to only 2/3 of 1 stick - reduce to only 1/2 cup of sugar (evaporated cane juice sugar is best) - recommended eggs - add an extra 2 medium sized very dark brown bananas (total of 4) - recommended flour - 2 teaspoons baking powder - 1 teaspoon salt - sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg or cardamom *BAKE AT: 375 for 30 min, then reduce to 350 for 25 minutes. Next time, I'll replace half of the AP flour with whole wheat, reduce baking powder to 1 tspn and will also reduce butter even further. I'm still in need of a delicious vegan, low-fat and low-sugar recipe.

