i only gave this recipe 2 forks because it required so many changes but figured i'd give my changes so someone wanting to make banana bread could make a decent one. First off, I'd put about 4 almost black bananas in. For the reviewers saying there was no banana flavor it must be because the bananas were not black enough to give that intense banana flavor. Also i wouldn't bother with white sugar at all, just use brown. It needs 2 t. of baking powder (so it's not so dense) and 1 t. of soda and 1 t. salt (i'm amazed it didn't have any). 1 t. vanilla and only 1 egg. I use texas muffin pans(extra large!) because i like the crust! :) If you make muffins it only needs 20-25 min on 400. hope this helps!

