Rating: 3
With a few changes I made this bread into something my picky girlfriend LOVED. She devoured most of the loaf in 2 days. The changes were: used 1/2 cup packed brown sugar and 1/2 cup white, I added 1/2 t vanilla and 1/4 t cinnamon, I omitted the nuts and added about 8 oz of semi-sweet mini chocolate chips. Also I used 3 black, previously frozen banannas that came to just over 1 cup when mashed. I find it to be an excellent starter bread for playing around with ingredients. Next I plan to reduce the choco chips and add chunky peanut butter. Yum!

