Rating: 4
Had this recipe for 2 years. Everyone rates this recipe as the best banana bread they've eaten. I can't understand why some people say it doesn't have enough banana flavor. Mine has a lot of banana flavor and is very moist. I have tried a lot of banana bread recipes, but this recipe is the best of all that I have tried in the past. I omitted the nuts because I prefer not to have nuts in my banana bread. I have to say that this recipe is better than the other banana breads purchased at reputable coffee shops and upscale bakeries in the bay area. The key to having good banana flavor is having overripe black bananas. The key for a moist bread is not to overmix.

