Wow! Easy and yummy! The only little problem was that I used a glass pan, and, after an hour at 350, it was golden on the outside and not at all done in the middle. So I turned down the heat to 325, baked another 20 or so minutes til the tester came out clean. It didn't burn and, boy, was the crust DELISH!!! I don't usually like banana bread - it is usually too dense and heavy. But this was surprisingly good, and not too heavy. This was my first banana-nut bread ever!!! And I shall definitely be making it again.

